    <node id="decision:0001">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Use Medbrief's existing Document Intelligence OCR output as PoV input</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:03", "chapter:04", "chapter:11"]</data>
      <data key="d15">person:joao-margura</data>
      <data key="d16">Medbrief already OCR-processes handwritten notes via Document Intelligence; reusing this avoids re-implementing handwriting OCR which is explicitly out of scope.</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "are you guys already doing OCR on the hand reading? If so, can we use this OCR on our project? Yes. Okay, okay, that helps a lot.", "ts": 211, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "as you are already doing OCR on this, I don't see why we cannot just use that. Out of scope is us doing the OCR and doing the fine-tuning of handwriting documents", "ts": 850, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0002">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Limit PoV to one medical domain to keep scope bounded</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:02", "chapter:03"]</data>
      <data key="d15">person:joao-margura</data>
      <data key="d16">Fixed-fee proposal requires quantification and bounded scope; one domain enables end-to-end proof before scaling.</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "we are proposing to select one domain... One medical domain: ex. hernia surgery.", "ts": 61, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0003">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Medbrief is responsible for obtaining the NICE API key</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:03", "chapter:04"]</data>
      <data key="d15">person:joao-margura</data>
      <data key="d16">NICE has compliance requirements for API access; Medbrief already holds relevant certifications and can obtain the key faster. Kumulus will support technical validation once access is granted.</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "it's an assumption that I'm making is that it's Matt Brief responsibility to get the API key. Because, you know, this can take some time.", "ts": 234, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0004">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Select the simplest case with the fewest NICE guideline references for the PoV</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:04"]</data>
      <data key="d15">person:joao-margura</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "I suggest we select, you know, kind of a simple case and does not have like... Dozens of guidelines, because we really want to streamline the whole process and make sure it works before we start expanding", "ts": 430, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0005">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Databricks chosen over Microsoft Fabric for parallel processing</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
