    <node id="visual:0013">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Step 1: NICE Data Acquisition</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "STEP 1: NICE DATA ACQUISITION\nStrategy &amp; Extraction\nPrimary Access: NICE API. Medbrief leads access, Kumulus supports technical validation.\nData Points: Guidelines, conditions, recommendations, metadata, version, and effective date.\nPoV Scope: One medical category; current and 2020 historical versions.\nStorage: Structured format with version and date metadata for precise alignment.\nWHY CURRENT AND 2020 GUIDELINE VERSIONS ARE USED\nThe goal is to prove the solution can handle guideline versioning, not just the future. A case must be compared against the guideline valid at the time of the clinical event. This prevents applying the wrong medical guidance to the wrong point in time.\nData Acquisition Flow\nNICE API\nREPOSITORY\nVERSIONS (CURRENT/2020)\nCASE-DATE MATCHING", "ts": 1024.93, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:05"]</data>
      <data key="d37">chapframe-05.png</data>
      <data key="d28">1024.93</data>
      <data key="d38">slide</data>
      <data key="d39">STEP 1: NICE DATA ACQUISITION
Strategy &amp; Extraction
Primary Access: NICE API. Medbrief leads access, Kumulus supports technical validation.
Data Points: Guidelines, conditions, recommendations, metadata, version, and effective date.
PoV Scope: One medical category; current and 2020 historical versions.
Storage: Structured format with version and date metadata for precise alignment.
WHY CURRENT AND 2020 GUIDELINE VERSIONS ARE USED
The goal is to prove the solution can handle guideline versioning, not just the future. A case must be compared against the guideline valid at the time of the clinical event. This prevents applying the wrong medical guidance to the wrong point in time.
Data Acquisition Flow
NICE API
REPOSITORY
VERSIONS (CURRENT/2020)
CASE-DATE MATCHING</data>
      <data key="d29">Architecture slide for Step 1 of the proposed pipeline: acquiring NICE guideline data via the NICE API (Medbrief leads access, Kumulus supports technical validation). Shows a data acquisition flow diagram: NICE API → Repository → Versions (Current/2020) → Case-Date Matching. Explains why both current and 2020 versions are used (case must be evaluated against the guideline valid at the time of the clinical event).</data>
      <data key="d40">8e28363636363434</data>
    </node>
