    <node id="visual:0016">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Step 5: Case vs NICE Guideline Comparison</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "STEP 5: CASE VS NICE GUIDELINE COMPARISON\n\nLogic &amp; Reasoning\n• Logic: Retrieve the applicable NICE guideline version based on the case date (Current or 2020).\n• Comparison: Compare extracted case facts and timeline against guideline recommendations.\n• Reasoning: Use AI to identify alignment or deviations, providing evidence-backed rationale.\n• Explainability: Include direct references to the source document and page number.\n\nNICE GUIDELINE (2020)\n\"Recommended surgical intervention for inguinal hernia in adults is...\"\n\nVS\n\nPATIENT CASE FACTS\n\"Surgery performed on 15/06/2020 using technique X...\"\n\nASSESSMENT RESULT: ALIGNED / DEVIATED\n(Evidence: Case_Doc_01, Page 4)", "ts": 1944.062, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:06"]</data>
      <data key="d37">frame-00015.png</data>
      <data key="d28">1944.062</data>
      <data key="d38">slide</data>
      <data key="d39">STEP 5: CASE VS NICE GUIDELINE COMPARISON

Logic &amp; Reasoning
• Logic: Retrieve the applicable NICE guideline version based on the case date (Current or 2020).
• Comparison: Compare extracted case facts and timeline against guideline recommendations.
• Reasoning: Use AI to identify alignment or deviations, providing evidence-backed rationale.
• Explainability: Include direct references to the source document and page number.

NICE GUIDELINE (2020)
"Recommended surgical intervention for inguinal hernia in adults is..."

VS

PATIENT CASE FACTS
"Surgery performed on 15/06/2020 using technique X..."

ASSESSMENT RESULT: ALIGNED / DEVIATED
(Evidence: Case_Doc_01, Page 4)</data>
      <data key="d29">Slide detailing the logic and reasoning for comparing extracted patient case facts against the applicable NICE guideline version, with an example showing alignment or deviation assessment with source evidence. Presenter is Joao (John) Margura.</data>
      <data key="d40">8604643424240024</data>
    </node>
    <node id="visual:0017">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Data Flow Diagram</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "DATA FLOW DIAGRAM\n\nSOURCES &gt; ORCHESTRATION &gt; PROCESSING &gt; ENGINE &gt; OUTCOME\nNICE API | Data Factory Movement &amp; Triggers | Databricks Entity Resolution Pseudonymisation | Case vs Guideline Comparison AI Reasoning | Evidence-Backed Assessment Explainable Output\nCase\nPDFs\nOCR\nOutput\n\nSecurity First: The storage layer separates raw evidence from secure identity mapping. AI processing receives only pseudonymized content.\n\nTraceability: The final output provides deviation, explanation, and supporting evidence with direct references to source documents.", "ts": 2034.5, "source": "vision"}]</data>
