    </node>
    <node id="visual:0018">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Case vs NICE Guideline Logic</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "CASE VS NICE GUIDELINE LOGIC\n\n1. IDENTIFY CONTEXT\n• Select the case.\n• Confirm selected medical domain.\n• Extract date and timeline references.\n\n2. SELECT VERSION\n• Retrieve applicable guideline by topic/date.\n• Compare current vs historical availability.\n\n3. EXTRACT FACTS\n• Identify clinical events.\n• Identify entities (Patient, Doctor, etc.).\n• Extract evidence from documents.\n\n4. COMPARE\n• What did guideline expect?\n• What does case show?\n• Identify alignment or deviation.\n\n5. OUTPUT\n• Assessment result and reasoning.\n• Evidence references.\n• Traceability to page.", "ts": 2293.0, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:08"]</data>
      <data key="d37">chapframe-08.png</data>
      <data key="d28">2293.0</data>
      <data key="d38">slide</data>
      <data key="d39">CASE VS NICE GUIDELINE LOGIC

1. IDENTIFY CONTEXT
• Select the case.
• Confirm selected medical domain.
• Extract date and timeline references.

2. SELECT VERSION
• Retrieve applicable guideline by topic/date.
• Compare current vs historical availability.

3. EXTRACT FACTS
• Identify clinical events.
• Identify entities (Patient, Doctor, etc.).
• Extract evidence from documents.

4. COMPARE
• What did guideline expect?
• What does case show?
• Identify alignment or deviation.

5. OUTPUT
• Assessment result and reasoning.
• Evidence references.
• Traceability to page.</data>
      <data key="d29">Five-step process flow for the case vs NICE guideline comparison logic: Identify Context, Select Version, Extract Facts, Compare, and Output. This defines the AI reasoning chain used to produce alignment or deviation assessments. Presenter is Joao (John) Margura.</data>
      <data key="d40">9c18225c4c040004</data>
    </node>
    <node id="visual:0019">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Success Criteria</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\nCRITERION | DESCRIPTION | TARGET / KPI | VALIDATION\nNICE Access | API access and feasibility validated. | Standard guideline samples retrieved. | Technical summary.\nCase Ingestion | Selected case PDFs are processed. | 1-2 surgery cases of the same medical domain processed. | OCR/Metadata review.\nText Preparation | Text extracted, cleaned, and chunked. | Content available for downstream AI. | Dataset review.\nEntity Extraction | Patients, doctors, and orgs identified. | Key entities extracted from documents. | Manual review.\nIdentity Resolution | Entity references linked via signals. | Name-only matching is avoided. | Rule review.\nPseudonymisation | Sensitive entities replaced before AI. | Consistent tokenisation across occurrences. | Consistency test.\nVersioning | Correct version selected by date. | Current and 2020 handling demonstrated. | Selection test.\nComparison | Facts compared against NICE rules. | Initial assessment generated for case. | Stakeholder review.\nExplainability | Outputs include evidence and rationale. | Assessment includes doc/page support. | Final demo review.", "ts": 2593.5, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:09"]</data>
      <data key="d37">chapframe-09.png</data>
      <data key="d28">2593.5</data>
      <data key="d38">slide</data>
      <data key="d39">SUCCESS CRITERIA

CRITERION | DESCRIPTION | TARGET / KPI | VALIDATION
NICE Access | API access and feasibility validated. | Standard guideline samples retrieved. | Technical summary.
Case Ingestion | Selected case PDFs are processed. | 1-2 surgery cases of the same medical domain processed. | OCR/Metadata review.
Text Preparation | Text extracted, cleaned, and chunked. | Content available for downstream AI. | Dataset review.
Entity Extraction | Patients, doctors, and orgs identified. | Key entities extracted from documents. | Manual review.
Identity Resolution | Entity references linked via signals. | Name-only matching is avoided. | Rule review.
Pseudonymisation | Sensitive entities replaced before AI. | Consistent tokenisation across occurrences. | Consistency test.
Versioning | Correct version selected by date. | Current and 2020 handling demonstrated. | Selection test.
Comparison | Facts compared against NICE rules. | Initial assessment generated for case. | Stakeholder review.
Explainability | Outputs include evidence and rationale. | Assessment includes doc/page support. | Final demo review.</data>
      <data key="d29">Table listing seven success criteria (NICE Access, Case Ingestion, Text Preparation, Entity Extraction, Pseudonymisation, Versioning, Comparison, Explainability) with descriptions, target KPIs, and validation methods. This defines the measurable acceptance criteria for the POV engagement. Presenter is Joao (John) Margura.</data>
      <data key="d40">e83456544c240004</data>
    </node>
    <node id="visual:0020">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Engagement Timeline</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d9">[{"quote": "ENGAGEMENT TIMELINE\n\nKickoff &amp; Alignment — Confirm goals, stakeholders, case documents, and NICE category.\nEnvironment Readiness — Weeks 1-2 — Prepare Data Factory, Databricks, and storage structure.\nNICE Integration — Weeks 3-5 — Validate API feasibility and review guideline content.\nCase Data Processing — Weeks 5-7 — Process PDFs via OCR, load, clean, and preserve metadata.\nEntity &amp; Pseudonymisation — Weeks 7-8 — Extract patients, resolve identities, and apply pseudonyms.\nComparison &amp; Findings — Weeks 8-10 — Structure logic, generate results, and present final summary.", "ts": 2879.5, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d7">["chapter:10"]</data>
      <data key="d37">chapframe-10.png</data>
      <data key="d28">2879.5</data>
      <data key="d38">diagram</data>
      <data key="d39">ENGAGEMENT TIMELINE

Kickoff &amp; Alignment — Confirm goals, stakeholders, case documents, and NICE category.
Environment Readiness — Weeks 1-2 — Prepare Data Factory, Databricks, and storage structure.
NICE Integration — Weeks 3-5 — Validate API feasibility and review guideline content.
Case Data Processing — Weeks 5-7 — Process PDFs via OCR, load, clean, and preserve metadata.
Entity &amp; Pseudonymisation — Weeks 7-8 — Extract patients, resolve identities, and apply pseudonyms.
Comparison &amp; Findings — Weeks 8-10 — Structure logic, generate results, and present final summary.</data>
      <data key="d29">Gantt-style timeline spanning approximately 10 weeks across six phases: Kickoff &amp; Alignment, Environment Readiness (Weeks 1-2), NICE Integration (Weeks 3-5), Case Data Processing (Weeks 5-7), Entity &amp; Pseudonymisation (Weeks 7-8), and Comparison &amp; Findings (Weeks 8-10). Sets clear delivery expectations for the POV engagement. Presenter is Joao (John) Margura.</data>
